@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor Student
actor "Assignment-owning Lecturer" as Lecturer
actor Admin

rectangle EduSecure {
  usecase "Authenticate" as UC1
  usecase "Complete MFA Challenge" as UC2
  usecase "Submit Assignment" as UC3
  usecase "Review Submission\nIntegrity Status" as UC4
  usecase "Retrieve Submission\nContent (audited)" as UC5
  usecase "Create / Update Grade" as UC6
}

Student --> UC1
Student --> UC2
Student --> UC3
Student --> UC5 : own submission only

Lecturer --> UC1
Lecturer --> UC4
Lecturer --> UC5
Lecturer --> UC6

Admin --> UC1
Admin --> UC4 : oversight
Admin --> UC5 : oversight
Admin --> UC6 : oversight

UC2 ..> UC1 : <<extends>> when MFA is enabled
UC5 ..> UC4 : <<separate endpoint>>
UC6 ..> UC4 : <<uses verified submission state>>

note bottom of EduSecure
This simplified current-state use-case diagram is intended for the final report.
It keeps the focus on implemented protected interactions:
cookie-backed authentication, optional TOTP MFA, submission upload,
separate audited content retrieval, and verified-submission grade handling.
Audit logs are written for sensitive actions, but public audit-review
endpoints remain deferred in the current repository.
end note
@enduml

